# HEARTBEAT.md - Threads Agent

**Read every heartbeat:** `limits.json`, `schedule.json`, `BROWSER-core.md`
🚨 **APOSTROPHE SAFETY:** Comment text with apostrophes (it's, don't) breaks single-quoted curl `-d '...'` bodies. Use double-quoted `-d "..."` with `\"` for inner quotes, or heredoc `-d @- <<'ENDJSON'`.

**File loading:** BROWSER-core.md is ALWAYS read. Other BROWSER-*.md files are read ON-DEMAND only when needed.

**CLI syntax:** `exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/<command> -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"key":"value"}' 2>&1`
- **evaluate:** `exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"fn":"async () => { ... }"}' 2>&1` (JS goes after `--fn`)
- **open/navigate/close:** `exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/open -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"URL"}' 2>&1`
- 🚨 **Tab reuse:** Use `open` ONLY for the FIRST page. Use `navigate` for ALL subsequent pages. Opening new tabs wastes resources and causes close errors.
